post_text: If you receive or have received a P-EBT card in the mail with your child‚Äôs name, please do not throw it away. It is not a scam. Jennings Public Schools is a Provision 2 school. This means all students eat breakfast & lunch for free. Because of this all students from last year qualified to receive a P-EBT card with $251 preloaded on there. It was provided as a COVID relief benefit for meals your child missed at school from March-May during the mandatory closure. It is our understanding that if you have more than one child, that the oldest child will receive a card, but it will be preloaded with $251 x the number of kids you have in our school.

Our calendar has changed slightly. There has been 8 distance learning Fridays added throughout the year. We will still have traditional in school instruction the same number of days as before. This will allow our students and teachers to practice a distance learning day a few times in case of an emergency shutdown.

In addition, it also allowed our day has been shortened. The first bell will now ring at 7:55 AM. Tardy bell will ring at 8:00 AM. School will he dismissed at 3:30 PM. We are also adding 10 minutes to lunch to better allow for social distancing in the cafeteria.

We have received several questions regarding this....

This highlights proposed CDC guidelines but are a long ways from being official. We are confident that many of the things listed here will likely not come to fruition.

While we anticipate there will be changes of some sort coming when school resumes in August, there is simply too much time between now & then to know exactly what this will look like at this time.

Obviously, student safety will continue to be our number one priority. As things progress & the picture becomes clearer, we will pass information along to our families & community.

We are opening up early Pre-Kindergarten enrollment & open transfer period for the 2020-2021 school year beginning today through Thursday, May 28th. Must turn 4 prior to September 1, 2020 to be eligible.

Enrollment packets can be picked up at the office. Office hours are Monday - Thursday from 9 AM - 2 PM. They are also available for download on our school website.

We will need copies of birth certificate, shot records, & social security cards. Contact Mr Meador at 918-757-2536 for additional information.

Feel free to share this with anyone you know who has a child ready to enter PK.

post_text:
PreK Graduation tonight @ 7 PM

Important Information:

* Arrive early. Parking will be limited. Park in the lot south of the gym.

*We ask that everyone remain in the vehicles at all times adhering to social distancing protocol.

*Tune your radio stations to 87.7. The broadcast will begin right at 7 PM. If you have any issues connecting, turn your radio off and back on.

*The ceremony will be done in two phases. Phase 1 will take about 15 minutes in the gym parking lot. There will be a 7-10 minute transition time to prepare for the parade.

*Phase 2 - Parents line up down Oak Street behind DAVCO. There will be a police escort through town. All other cars can line main street for the graduation parade. Please do not park directly in front of city hall. This is where we will be handing out diplomas at the end of the parade. The parade will start approximately 7-10 minutes after phase 1 ends.

*The parade will end after the last graduate receives their diploma.

Parents: Robin & David Bates

Grandparents: Francis Croft

Autumn's Favorite Jennings Memory.........."When Alex wrote on his "get to know each other" paper in 6th grade he liked to work and Mr. Humble could not stop laughing. I never saw him laugh so hard in the 3 years I have known him."

Autumn Would Like to Tell Her Classmates.........."I hope you are staying safe and I wish them the best in life. I hope all your dreams come true."

Final Thoughts?.........."I would like to thank my teachers. They have been there for me in every way possible. Without them I wouldn't be where I am today. I would also like to thank Mr. Reeves for keeping me sane this year!"

If you cannot make it during than window, please call the school at 918-757-2536 to make other arrangements. They are also available to download & print directly from our website.

Online learning assignment lists will also be available to be picked up during that time or you can download them directly from our distance learning resource page.

post_text: Please take the time to complete the census! It‚Äôs important for future funding for our school!
shared_text:
Oklahoma State Department of Education
April 1 at 6:03 PM ¬∑

Today is Census Day! Complete the Census online in approximately five minutes or less at 2020census.gov.

The Census determines how much federal funding and services our towns, cities and schools (!) receive each year for the next decade.

Each undercounted person means an estimated $1,675 less per year (or $16,750 per person in Oklahoma over the next 10 years) in lost funding, grants and support for our communities ‚Äì so accurate representation is important!

Curious as to how much YOUR county stands to lose if citizens are undercounted? Check out the dollar figures here: https://okletscount.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Oklahoma-Census-Undercount-Cost-by-County.pdf
